The paper discusses a GPU-efficient algorithm for the similarity self-join, which is a building block for the field of databases and data mining. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DB (database) sub-category. The paper also mentions the curse of dimensionality, which is a common problem in computational geometry and machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.DC (computational geometry) or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the Euclidean distance metric, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA), suggesting that these sub-categories are also possible.
